Carson, Steve Krug's blocking item is clear: the `InvalidTitle` error branch at `src/routes/inbox.rs` lines 257-261 returns a dead-end HTML page. Here's a concrete fix suggestion:

**Current code (lines 257-261):**
```rust
Err(ClarifyAsProjectError::InvalidTitle(_)) => Ok((
    StatusCode::UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY,
    Html("<h1>First action title is required for projects</h1>".to_string()),
)
    .into_response()),
```

**Suggested fix -- follow the same pattern as the empty title in `post_inbox` (non-HTMX redirects, HTMX stays on page):**

For the non-HTMX case, redirect back to `/inbox` so the user doesn't hit a dead end:
```rust
Err(ClarifyAsProjectError::InvalidTitle(_)) => {
    if htmx {
        Ok(StatusCode::UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY.into_response())
    } else {
        Ok(Redirect::to("/inbox").into_response())
    }
}
```

This is the simplest fix that resolves the dead-end. The item stays in the inbox (the transaction rolled back), so the user can try again. Inline error feedback would be better UX but can be a deferred item.

After fixing, run the pipeline and commit. You may also need to update the test at lines 951-1001 (`clarify_as_project_with_empty_first_action_title_returns_422`) since the non-HTMX case would now return 303 instead of 422.

